description:
### PhoneCall

The method phoneCall takes in four integers representing the costs of certain minutes of a phone call and the total amount of money and returns the total minutes of phone call that can be made within the budget.

Input: Four integers min1, min2_10, min11, s where min1 represents cost of first minute, min2_10 is the cost of second to tenth minutes, min11 is the cost after tenth minute and s is the total amount of money. (0 ≤ min1 ≤ 10, 0 ≤ min2_10 ≤ 10, 0 ≤ min11 ≤ 10, 1 ≤ s ≤ 30)
Output: An integer represents the total minutes of phone call the user can make.

Example:

```js phoneCall(3, 1, 2, 20) // 14 ```
